<br>
We kill mobs based on three things: 1) amount of people on, 2) the usefulness of the mob's drops, 3) the amount of time the raid will take.<br>
<br>
Based on the amount of people we had on (~35) and the very limited time (since it was very late) that sorta limited what we could kill.  Then when you think about how useful Cazic Thule's drops are to us, it wasn't even a choice.<br>
<br>
Now come and flame me because I didn't say 'fun' anywhere.  Sure, that fight was hella fun, but my guild becoming stronger is worth more than fun to me.  Those items that Cazic Thule dropped definately helped.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry that our selfishness got in the way of your fun, but there are many single player games out there that you can play for fun without having to worry about being the best.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm asking you why you pursued a mob 63 people were attempting<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Because we could.  Cazic Thule was not aggro'd when I pulled him, therefor your being there or not made no difference, well except for the lag.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> How would it hurt your fun if they failed and then called more reinforcements, maybe took him down 5 attempts and 8h later with 200 people. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Clearing fear is not fun for anyone, and any chance we'd get to skip that I'd jump at.  We had had a long day, Yelinak was before we went to fear, and that is by no means an easy fight.  We were all very tired, and were not going to be up 8 hours later waiting for reinforcements to be grown.<br>
<br>
